  "tutorial/body-nested-models::section-0003": {
    "node_id": "tutorial/body-nested-models::section-0003",
    "parent_id": "tutorial/body-nested-models::section-0001",
    "level": 2,
    "node_kind": "heading",
    "heading_text": "List fields with type parameter",
    "anchor_id": "list-fields-with-type-parameter",
    "section_url": "https://fastapi.tiangolo.com/tutorial/body-nested-models/#list-fields-with-type-parameter",
    "section_text": "But Python has a specific way to declare lists with internal types, or \"type parameters\":",
    "section_inline_code": [],
    "section_links": [],
    "code_refs": [],
    "code_blocks": []
  },
  "tutorial/body-nested-models::section-0004": {
    "node_id": "tutorial/body-nested-models::section-0004",
    "parent_id": "tutorial/body-nested-models::section-0003",
    "level": 3,
    "node_kind": "heading",
    "heading_text": "Declare a list with a type parameter",
    "anchor_id": "declare-a-list-with-a-type-parameter",
    "section_url": "https://fastapi.tiangolo.com/tutorial/body-nested-models/#declare-a-list-with-a-type-parameter",
    "section_text": "To declare types that have type parameters (internal types), like list , dict , tuple , pass the internal type(s) as \"type parameters\" using square brackets: [ and ]\n\nThat's all standard Python syntax for type declarations.\n\nUse that same standard syntax for model attributes with internal types.\n\nSo, in our example, we can make tags be specifically a \"list of strings\":",
    "section_inline_code": [
      "list",
      "dict",
      "tuple",
      "[",
      "]",
      "tags"
    ],
    "section_links": [],
    "code_refs": [
      {
        "type": "code_ref",
        "path": "../../docs_src/body_nested_models/tutorial002_py310.py",
        "highlight_lines": [
          12
        ],
        "raw": "{* ../../docs_src/body_nested_models/tutorial002_py310.py hl[12] *}",
        "section_id": "tutorial/body-nested-models::section-0004",
        "section_url": "https://fastapi.tiangolo.com/tutorial/body-nested-models/#declare-a-list-with-a-type-parameter"
      }
    ],
    "code_blocks": [
      {
        "type": "code_block",
        "language": "Python",
        "text": "my_list: list[str]",
        "section_id": "tutorial/body-nested-models::section-0004",
        "section_url": "https://fastapi.tiangolo.com/tutorial/body-nested-models/#declare-a-list-with-a-type-parameter"
      }
    ]
  },
  "tutorial/body-nested-models::section-0005": {
    "node_id": "tutorial/body-nested-models::section-0005",
    "parent_id": "tutorial/body-nested-models::section-0001",
    "level": 2,
    "node_kind": "heading",
    "heading_text": "Set types",
    "anchor_id": "set-types",
    "section_url": "https://fastapi.tiangolo.com/tutorial/body-nested-models/#set-types",
    "section_text": "But then we think about it, and realize that tags shouldn't repeat, they would probably be unique strings.\n\nAnd Python has a special data type for sets of unique items, the set .\n\nThen we can declare tags as a set of strings:\n\nWith this, even if you receive a request with duplicate data, it will be converted to a set of unique items.\n\nAnd whenever you output that data, even if the source had duplicates, it will be output as a set of unique items.\n\nAnd it will be annotated / documented accordingly too.",
    "section_inline_code": [
      "set",
      "tags"
    ],
    "section_links": [],
    "code_refs": [
      {
        "type": "code_ref",
        "path": "../../docs_src/body_nested_models/tutorial003_py310.py",
        "highlight_lines": [
          12
        ],
        "raw": "{* ../../docs_src/body_nested_models/tutorial003_py310.py hl[12] *}",
        "section_id": "tutorial/body-nested-models::section-0005",
        "section_url": "https://fastapi.tiangolo.com/tutorial/body-nested-models/#set-types"
      }
    ],
    "code_blocks": []
  },
  "tutorial/body-nested-models::section-0006": {
    "node_id": "tutorial/body-nested-models::section-0006",
    "parent_id": "tutorial/body-nested-models::section-0001",
    "level": 2,
    "node_kind": "heading",
    "heading_text": "Nested Models",
    "anchor_id": "nested-models",
    "section_url": "https://fastapi.tiangolo.com/tutorial/body-nested-models/#nested-models",
    "section_text": "Each attribute of a Pydantic model has a type.\n\nBut that type can itself be another Pydantic model.\n\nSo, you can declare deeply nested JSON \"objects\" with specific attribute names, types and validations.\n\nAll that, arbitrarily nested.",
    "section_inline_code": [],
    "section_links": [],
    "code_refs": [],
    "code_blocks": []
  },
